author: Javier E. David
title: Royal Wedding: Prince Harry marries Meghan Markle
text:
A Royal Wedding: Prince Harry marries Meghan Markle at Windsor Castle Matt Cardy | Getty Images Javier E. David | Adam Jeffery 41 Mins Ago
Prince Harry, grandson to Queen Elizabeth II, married American actress Meghan Markle on Saturday, in a ceremony that took place at St George's Chapel at Windsor Castle.
The wedding was a global affair, with thousands camped out along the procession route to Windsor Castle. Around the world, millions were watching on television â€” even in the wee hours of the morning, or late at night in some time zones. The Bride with her mother
Meghan Markle (pictured, right) with her mother Doria Ragland drive down the Long Walk as they arrive at Windsor Castle ahead of her wedding to Prince Harry. Richard Heathcote | Getty Images Two Princes
Prince Harry walks with his best man, Prince William, the Duke of Cambridge, as they arrive at St George's Chapel at Windsor Castle. Chris Radburn | WPA | Getty Images The bride arrives
Meghan Markle arrives at St George's Chapel, dazzling onlookers in a dress designed by Clare Waight Keller, the British artistic director of France's fashion powerhouse, Givenchy. Andrew Matthews | Reuters The walk down the aisle
Meghan Markle (center) walks down the aisle in St. George's Chapel, Windsor Castle, in Windsor, on during her wedding to Britain's Prince Harry, Duke of Sussex. Danny Lawson | AFP | Getty Images Prince Charles accompanies the bride
Prince Harry looks at his bride, Meghan Markle, as she arrives accompanied by the Prince of Wales. Health troubles forced Markle's biological father to miss the ceremony. Jonathan Brady | Reuters Queen Elizabeth II and Prince Phillip
Queen Elizabeth II and Prince Phillip look on during the wedding service for Prince Harry and Meghan Markle at St George's Chapel. Jonathan Brady | Reuters
Prince Harry looks at his bride, Meghan Markle, as she arrives. Jonathan Brady | Reuters Wedding ceremony
Prince Harry and Meghan Markle during their wedding service, conducted by the Archbishop of Canterbury Justin Welby. Owen Humphreys | Reuters Husband and wife
Prince Harry, Duke of Sussex and his wife Meghan, Duchess of Sussex emerge from the West Door of St George's Chapel. Ben The Kiss
Britain's Prince Harry, Duke of Sussex kisses his wife Meghan, Duchess of Sussex, as they leave from the West Door of St George's Chapel, Windsor Castle. Ben Stansall | AFP | Getty Images Royal Procession
Prince Harry, Duke of Sussex and Meghan, Duchess of Sussex leave Windsor Castle in the Ascot Landau carriage during a procession after getting married at St Georges Chapel. Samir Hussein | WireImage | Getty Images Newlyweds
Prince Harry, Duke of Sussex and Meghan, Duchess of Sussex leave Windsor Castle in the Ascot Landau carriage. Mark R. Milan | GC Images | Getty Images Brits celebrate
Britain's Prince Harry, Duke of Sussex kisses his wife Meghan, Duchess of Sussex as they leave from the West Door of St George's Chapel, Windsor Castle, in Windsor after their wedding ceremony. Danny Lawson | AFP | Getty Images
